Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '198', circled. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 116, 16? Name Armosilas. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX F 051.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0693)
